In this section, we present a way to encode binary RTCNs, that is, a way to describe binary RTCNs in such a way that two RTCNs are the same if and only if they have the same description. The encoding itself is a straight-forward translation of the process described in Sect. 2 for generating a binary RTCN into the language of collections of subsets of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
