fn.p:
We summarize the argument for those readers familiar with the theory of posets: Consider the order complex of the poset \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$(\mathfrak {T}(X),\preceq )$$\end{document}. The fact that every order complex is a flag complex implies, by a classical result of Gromov (1987), that the orthant space is CAT(0).
